snippet: The Ensemble ACJW played works by Georg Friedrich Haas, Mozart and Schoenberg on Friday as part of Carnegie Hall’s Vienna: City of Dreams festival.
abstract: James R Oestreich reviews performance by Ensemble ACJW, playing works by Georg Friedrich Haas, Mozart and Schoenberg, at Weill Recital Hall as part of Carnegie Hall’s Vienna: City of Dreams festival.
lead_paragraph: The Ensemble ACJW played works by Georg Friedrich Haas, Mozart and Schoenberg on Friday as part of Carnegie Hall’s Vienna: City of Dreams festival.
